doc_description: ID in the PHANGS-HST candidate catalog for each individual target, for cross-identification.
ID in the initial PHANGS-HST “all-source” detection catalog for each individual target, for cross-identification.
X coordinates on HST X-pixel grid (0...n-1). Scale = 0.03962 arcsec/pixel.
Y coordinates on HST Y-pixel grid (0...n-1). Scale = 0.03962 arcsec/pixel.

J2000 Declination, ICRS frame, calibrated against selected Gaia sources.
Human visual classification determined by Brad Whitmore (BCW). Further details in Whitmore et al. (2021) (2021MNRAS.506.5294W).
Classification determined by VGG neural network model of Hannon et al. (2023)

Quality value providing accuracy of the VGG neural network classification. The provided value lies between 0.3 and 1 and denotes the frequency of the classification among the 10 randomly initialized models.

An integer denoting the number of bands in which the photometry for the object was below the requested signal-to-noise ratio (S/N=1).
An integer denoting the number of bands for which the object was outside the footprint of the sky coverage.
Concentration index measured in F555W for aperture radii of 1 and 3 pixels.

String to identify in which region on the human-classified color-color diagram the object was associated with. Values are “YCL” (young cluster locus) “MAP” (middle-aged plume), “OGCC” (old globular cluster clump), or “outside” (outside the main regions and therefore not classified). A detailed description is found in Section 4.4. of Maschmann+24

String to identify in which region on the ML-classified color-color diagram the object was associated with. Values are “YCL” (young cluster locus) “MAP” (middle-aged plume), “OGCC” (old globular cluster clump), or “outside” (outside the main regions and therefore not classified). A detailed description is found in Section 4.4. of Maschmann+24
